<h2 class="my-5">How to form the <em>participe pass&eacute;</em></h2>
<p>For regular <em>er/ir/re</em>-verbs, the participe pass&eacute; is easy to construct:</p>
<ul>
  <li>If the infinitive ends in <strong>-er</strong>, the participle ends in <strong>&eacute;</strong></li>
  <em>Examples: aimer ➡ aim&eacute; / manger ➡ mang&eacute;</em>
  <li class="mt-3">If the infinitive ends in <strong>-ir</strong>, the participle ends in <strong>i</strong></li>
  <em>Examples: finir ➡ fini / sortir ➡ sorti</em>
  <li class="mt-3">If the infinitive ends in <strong>-re</strong>, the participle ends in <strong>u</strong></li>
  <em>Examples: vendre ➡ vendu</em>
</ul>
